ncdu Command (NCurses Disk Usage)

ncdu stands for NCurses Disk Usage.
It is a disk usage analyzer with an interactive UI in the terminal.

👉 It helps you quickly find which files/folders are taking up space on a Linux server.

Very useful in production servers when disk is full


fzf stands for Fuzzy Finder.

It is a command-line search tool that lets you interactively search files, commands, history, processes, Git branches, etc.



1) ncdu - folder size in order
2) tldr  - details of more commands
3) rg insane - To search for file or folder / grep 
4) fzf - search for files path
5) bat - to read the file


